Shades of Buchanan and Muses of Du Bartas turn here, not that the vales os Elysium may roll alost the eries of joy in their· bowery glades, but that the Cean dirge may chant for your king the farewell strain. Ay, dead is the king, the Peace Maker, best of Kings. All that wit, Prudence, &Vorth, the applause os the world, and Plenty with her horn could effect, was stored that our age should rejoicc in its peerless king. Why mention our age? I should doubt if his equal has ever lived. What of Alexander and Cacsar : thunderbolts of war, purchasing the bubble reputa- tion in streams of blood? But he had his name and glory frorn peace; such 1 may believe were the happier days os man in the reign of old Saturn, and such the early blooin of the age of gold. When Elizabeth sought the mansions of the blest‚ the nobles of England saluted him as Lord and King; thus with love and law <lid one win so many realmS.
